**Structured to object-oriented approach

Instead of separate functions for student data, we created a Student object.

Identifying objects and classes

We identified Student as the main class.

Representation of object and state

Each object stores:

name
rollNo
marks
grade
Simple class

We built a simple Student class.

Encapsulation

Data and methods are together in one class.

Data hiding

We used private.

Reading and writing objects

readData() and writeData() do that.

Class-level and instance-level members
instance: name, rollNo, marks, grade
class-level: studentCount
Debugging idea

