**Very short summary of why each major part exists:

Student class

To model the real-world student.

instance variables

To store each student’s own data.

private

To protect data.

static studentCount

To store class-wide common data.

constructor

To increase object count automatically.

readData()

To read object data.

calculateGrade()

To process object data.

writeData()

To display object data.

showStudentCount()

To show total objects created.

main()

To start program execution.

s1, s2

To create real objects from the class.
